### 🧠 When to Use Each One 🤔

| Scenario | Choice | Why |
|----------|--------|-----|
| **Quick prototyping** | Either is fine | Speed matters more than polish |
| **Production code** | `.expect()` | Better error messages for logs |
| **Library code** | Neither - use `?` | Libraries should propagate errors |
| **Test code** | Either is fine | Tests should panic on failure anyway |
| **Startup/validation** | `.expect()` | Clear failure messages are valuable |
| **User input handling** | Neither - proper error handling | Users expect graceful error handling |

