-- For each post, fetch author:
SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 1;  -- N queries (100 in this case)
SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 2;
SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 3;
-- ... 97 more queries!

-- ✅ GOOD: Single query with JOIN (1 query total!)
SELECT posts.*, users.name as author_name 
FROM posts 
JOIN users ON posts.author_id = users.id;
```

**Key insight**: Instead of N+1 queries, use **1 efficient query** with JOINs or batch loading! ✨

