### 🧠 W3C Integration Best Practices 🤔

| Practice | Recommendation | Why |
|----------|----------------|-----|
| **Always Propagate** | Forward traceparent headers | Maintain trace continuity |
| **Validate Format** | Check W3C compliance | Prevent malformed traces |
| **Respect Sampling** | Honor trace_flags sampling bit | Consistent sampling decisions |
| **Generate Secure IDs** | Use cryptographically secure RNG | Prevent trace ID collisions |
| **Handle Errors Gracefully** | Continue without tracing on errors | Don't break functionality |
| **Support tracestate** | Include vendor-specific context | Richer distributed context |
| **Log Trace Context** | Include trace IDs in logs | Better correlation |
| **Test Cross-System** | Verify with other W3C systems | Ensure compatibility |

